and then they let her go.

382
00:16:44,330 --> 00:16:45,780
-为什么  -她不告诉我
- Why? - She wouldn't tell me.

383
00:16:45,980 --> 00:16:47,740
就说老板是个变态
All she said was her boss was a creep.

384
00:16:55,690 --> 00:16:58,150
30分钟前  佐伊给我发了条短信
Thirty minutes ago, I received a text from Zoe.

385
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:00,510
毫无疑问  她想道歉
She intends to apologize, no doubt.

386
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:03,150
我尊重她想当面忏悔的意愿
I respect that she wants to atone in person,

387
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:06,540
尽管她花了16个小时才鼓起勇气
even though it's taken her over 16 hours to build up the courage.

388
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:24,520
简宁・斯克斯基正在调查彼得・罗素
Janine Skorsky is digging into Peter Russo.

389
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:27,390
具体什么方面
What in particular?

390
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,050
造船厂协会
The shipbuilders' association.

391
00:17:29,450 --> 00:17:30,410
她要怎么写
She have an angle?

392
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:34,010
流域法案是对他们失去工作的补偿
The watershed bill is a consolation prize for them losing their jobs.

393
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:35,590
这话说的有点道理
That's not an unfair assessment.

394
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,370
她认为如果法案没有通过
She thinks if the bill fails to pass,

395
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:38,800
