going to the floor later this week.

460
00:20:56,550 --> 00:20:59,310
-你有信心它会通过吗  -非常有信心
- Are you optimistic it'll pass? - I'm very optimistic.

461
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:01,670
《特拉华河流域法案》不仅能保护
The Delaware river watershed Act not only protects

462
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:04,060
州内大部分淡水资源
large portions of the state's freshwater resources,

463
00:21:04,070 --> 00:21:05,990
还能创造数以千计的工作岗位
it also creates thousands of jobs.

464
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,890
我有信心  国会的同事...
I'm confident that my colleagues on the Hill...

465
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:09,630
促进就业只有一个办法
There's only one way to create jobs.

466
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,180
我任州长时曾实施过
I did it during my administration.

467
00:21:11,190 --> 00:21:13,910
就是减免小公司的税额
The answer is tax credits for small businesses.

468
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:16,420
我们要鼓励白手起家的企业家们
You've got to encourage self-starting entrepreneurs

469
00:21:16,430 --> 00:21:17,520
经营新企业
to start new ventures,

470
00:21:17,530 --> 00:21:19,520
-雇佣员工  -具体地
- hire employees... - But specifically,

471
00:21:19,530 --> 00:21:21,030
-关于流域法案  -小公司
- about the watershed act... - Small businesses,

472
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:23,460
才是解决之道  其他都是在装门面
that's the solution. Everything else is window dressing.

473
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,740
非常感谢各位
Thank you all very much.

474
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:27,030
谢谢
Thank you.

475
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:29,860
晚安  副总统先生
Good night, Mr. Vice-President.

476
00:21:35,790 --> 00:21:36,460
你好
Hello.

477
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,160
我想谈谈马修斯
I need to talk about Matthews.

478
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:39,740
没错  我看过新闻报道了
Yes. I read the press reports.

479
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:41,560
他没帮上什么忙  是吗
He's not being very helpful, is he?

480
00:21:41,780 --> 00:21:43,150
他害多利少
He's doing more harm than good.

481
00:21:43,990 --> 00:21:45,230
我想让他离开
I want to ask him to leave.

482
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:46,890
那说出去可不好听
Well, that wouldn't make for a very good story.

483
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,060
那也比让他毁了整个巡回竞选强
It's better than him torpedoing the whole bus tour.

484
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:50,300
你有和他谈过吗
Have you tried to talk to him?

485
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:51,840
还没  我想先征求你的意见
No, I wanted to ask your advice first.

486
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:54,400
也许有办法
Well, maybe there's a way

487
00:21:54,410 --> 00:21:57,240
能不赶他走又让他支持你
to keep him on the tour and inspire his support.

488
00:21:57,290 --> 00:21:59,000
我们的观点存在本质差异
We have fundamentally different views.

489
00:21:59,460 --> 00:22:01,460
你无法改变他的观念
Well, look, you're not going to be able change his ideology,

490
00:22:01,470 --> 00:22:02,590
触动他的心
but dig deeper.

491
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:05,430
吉姆是个骄傲的人  从骄傲下手
Jim is a proud man. Tap into that pride.

492
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,090
我只想他走人
I just wish he was gone.

493
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,910
做你觉得最合适的事
Well, you do whatever you think best.

494
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,270
但无论决定怎样
But whatever it is you decide,

495
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:13,470
一定要坚守自己的立场
be firm and stand up for yourself.

496
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:15,070
至少他会对此有所回应
He'll respond to that at least.

497
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,740
还有需要  再给我打电话
And call me back if you need anything.

498
00:22:22,670 --> 00:22:24,980
他给的理由是什么  你闯祸了吗
What was the reason he gave you? Were you messing up?

499
00:22:25,170 --> 00:22:28,530
没有  领班说我做得很好
No. The head waiter said I was doing a really good job.

500
00:22:28,810 --> 00:22:31,300
他第二天甚至开始让我独自负责餐桌
He even started letting me take my own tables on the second day.

501
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:33,970
那就是经理  他叫什么
And then the manager... what's his name?

502
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,290
里昂
Leon.

503
00:22:37,170 --> 00:22:38,500
他调戏你了
He propositioned you?

504
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:40,560
他叫我去他办公室
Called me into his office,

505
00:22:40,570 --> 00:22:45,420
说不能再雇新员工了  甚至是兼职的
said couldn't afford to start taking anyone new on, even part-time.

506
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:50,530
他把手放在我的膝盖上  说可以有例外
Put his hand on my knee, said he might be able to make an exception.

507
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:53,470
然后他的手滑向了我的大腿
So he started sliding his hand up my thigh.

508
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,800
我站起来说要回去工作
So I stood up and I tell him I should get back to work.

509
00:22:56,720 --> 00:23:00,050
他说"留下"  解开了自己的皮带
He says, "Stay." He unbuckled his belt.

510
00:23:01,410 --> 00:23:02,160
你做了吗
Did you?

511
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,910
没有  我走出办公室  回去工作
No, I walked out of the office and got back to my tables.

512
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:12,300
第二天去上班时  他要我回家
Next day, I came into work, told me to go home.

513
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:13,560
我被辞退了
I was fired.

514
00:23:16,530 --> 00:23:17,990
告诉我餐馆的名字
Tell me the name of the restaurant.

515
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,300
你回家好早
You're home early.

516
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,630
我需要休息下
I needed a breather.

517
00:23:27,830 --> 00:23:28,980
今早我都没吃早饭
I didn't have breakfast this morning.

518
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:30,370
我过会儿可能还要回去
I might head back in a little while.

519
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:32,520
投票算得如何
The vote count?

520
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:37,420
这次得最后才见分晓了
It's going to come down to the wire on this one.

521
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:43,160
我今天和凯瑟琳・杜兰特谈过了
I spoke to Catherine Durant today.

522
00:23:43,780 --> 00:23:45,970
她无法将那批货运出南苏丹
She's unable to get the shipment out of South Sudan.

523
00:23:45,980 --> 00:23:47,750
是的  我们要断绝一切邦交
Yeah, we're cutting all diplomatic ties.

524
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,820
外事委员会对这事很恼火
Foreign Affairs is up in arms about it.

525
00:23:50,020 --> 00:23:53,530
对  据她说  因此她毫无办法
Yes. Which is why she can't lift a finger, according to her.

526
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:56,490
总之她是这么说的  你得去和她谈谈
It's what she said anyway. Anyway, I need you to talk to her.

527
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:58,170
我看那样也没什么用
I don't think that would make any difference.

528
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,890
她不是欠我们的吗  弗兰西斯
I thought she owed us, Francis.

529
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:01,830
